.TH hsh 1 "February 2026" "1.0" "Simple Shell Manual"
.SH NAME
hsh - simple UNIX command interpreter

.SH SYNOPSIS
.B hsh
.RI [ command ]

.SH DESCRIPTION
hsh is a simple UNIX command language interpreter written in C.

It reads commands from standard input and executes them.
The shell works in both interactive and non-interactive modes.

In interactive mode, hsh displays a prompt and waits for user input.

In non-interactive mode, hsh reads commands from standard input without displaying a prompt.

.SH INVOCATION
The shell can be invoked in the following ways:

Interactive mode:
.RS
./hsh
.RE

Non-interactive mode:
.RS
echo "/bin/ls" | ./hsh
.RE

.SH ENVIRONMENT
hsh uses the PATH environment variable to locate executable files.

.SH EXIT STATUS
hsh returns the exit status of the last executed command.

.SH AUTHORS
Tural Gasimov